Three of the four quarter-final pairings at the European Championships have been confirmed. In the first game, Spain will take on Switzerland. Both countries were involved in high-scoring thrillers on Monday evening. Spain threw away a 3-1 lead to draw 3-3 with Croatia. However, they were able to win 5-3 in extra time and progress in the competition. Belgium play Italy for a place in the Euro 2020 semi-final. The Red Devils eliminated Cristiano Ronaldo and Portugal, while Roberto Manciniâ€™s men sent Austria packing. Czech Republic will face Denmark in their quarter-final encounter. The last pairing will be decided today, after England vs Germany and Ukraine vs Sweden.